By IDRIS OLUKOYA EPE (LAGOS STATE )- Mr Monsuru Akinloye, Chairman, Eredo Local Council Development Area, Epe Division, Lagos State, has urged residents to pick up their Permanent Voters Cards (PVCs) at collection centres in the region.Akinloye made the plea in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Epe, on Friday.He said that there are lots of uncollected PVCs at the centres awaiting collection.Akinloye said that the voter’s card serves as weapons to vote out bad governance and to vote in good governance.“You can determine who leads the nation and your community through your voter’s card. Vote wisely and vote according to your conscience.“One man, one vote. Your voter card is the answer to elect responsive and reliable candidates to occupy the leadership positions in our dear country,” he said.The chairman said “Your voter’s card will make you eligible to vote into power your choice candidates.”Akinloye also appealed to those who are yet to register for their PVCs to do so before the deadline.“I and my family have done our registration and we have collected our PVCs, other residents and subordinates need to do so too.“We have different registration centres across the council area, therefore, residents can visit any of the centres for registration.” he said (NAN) By OLADAPO UDOM Mrs Ibijoke Sanwo-Olu LAGOS- Wife of Lagos Governor, Mrs Ibijoke Sanwo-Olu, has called on eligible voters, who have yet to get their permanent voter cards (PVCs) to do so without delay.Sanwo-Olu made the call at the Africa Bridge Initiative programme, held at Akerele Health Centre, Surulere.The News… In "News" By ANGELA ATABO ABUJA- NESSACTION, a Civil Society Organisation, in collaboration with INEC, on Tuesday launched Continuous Voter Registration (CRV) and Permanent Voters’ Cards (PVC) collection drive in 15 states.Executive Director NESSACTION, Mr Eniola  Cole,  said at the launch of the project on Tuesday in Abuja that the exercise was… In "News" By Eguonor Ighure Asaba-